<BaseLayout title="About">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>I'm Brigit Schroeder, a software engineer growing my data science skills with an emphasis in healthcare analytics.</p>
    <p>This site documents one hundred real investigations using public healthcare data. Each one starts with a genuine question — something I don't know the answer to — and works through the data honestly, including the dead ends and surprises.</p>
    <p>The tools: Python, SQL, pandas, scikit-learn, matplotlib, and Jupyter notebooks. The data: publicly available datasets from NHANES, SAMHSA, CMS, and others.</p>
    <h2>Why one hundred?</h2>
    <p>A hundred investigations is enough to build real fluency — not just with the tools, but with the thinking process behind good data analysis. The goal isn't a hundred perfect analyses. It's a hundred honest ones.</p>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Find me on <a href="https://github.com/brigitschroeder">GitHub</a>.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
